{"type":"text","timestamp":1775864059357,"sessionID":"ses_2864311fcffeWOvMZp4PBAzLBv","part":{"id":"prt_d79bf1118001fFKTyOKq2U5jfb","messageID":"msg_d79bf0545001hufa5h1TtOTXoE","sessionID":"ses_2864311fcffeWOvMZp4PBAzLBv","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the context. The user wants me to write a `design.md` document for AR-019 (CLI binary entry point) based on the specification in `.sdd_prompt.md`. This is for 4 CLI binaries in the agentcube project, with the client-go library already generated.","time":{"start":1775864059356,"end":1775864059356}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864160916,"sessionID":"ses_2864311fcffeWOvMZp4PBAzLBv","part":{"id":"prt_d79bf15de0014pm28vtQmT90A2","messageID":"msg_d79bf0545001hufa5h1TtOTXoE","sessionID":"ses_2864311fcffeWOvMZp4PBAzLBv","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_41dbb2595d0845d8849f1116","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/design.md","content":"# Design: AR-019 CLI Binary Entry Points\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for 4 CLI binaries in the agentcube project. These tools provide command-line interfaces for managing agentcube resources and interacting with the Kubernetes API.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Binary Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── agentd/                      # Kubernetes controller (existing)\n│   └── main.go\n├── agentcube/                   # Main CLI - resource management\n│   └── main.go\n├── agentcube-admin/             # Admin CLI - cluster administration\n│   └── main.go\n├── agentcube-shell/             # Interactive shell - sandbox access\n│   └── main.go\n└── agentcube-proxy/             # API proxy - local port forwarding\n    └── main.go\n```\n\n### Module Dependencies\n\n- **client-go**: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n  - Typed clients for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n  - Informers for watching resources\n  - Listers for cached read access\n- **controller-runtime**: Shared utilities for config, logging\n- **cobra**: CLI framework (all binaries)\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### agentcube (Main CLI)\n\n```go\ntype CLI struct {\n    clientset     versioned.Interface\n    informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n    namespace     string\n    outputFormat  string\n}\n\ntype SandboxOptions struct {\n    Name           string\n    Namespace      string\n    RuntimeType    string\n    CPURequest     string\n    MemoryRequest  string\n    Labels         map[string]string\n    Annotations    map[string]string\n    Timeout        time.Duration\n}\n\ntype RuntimeOptions struct {\n    Name          string\n    Namespace     string\n    Spec          runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec\n    Timeout       time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n### agentcube-admin (Admin CLI)\n\n```go\ntype AdminCLI struct {\n    clientset     versioned.Interface\n    kubeClient    kubernetes.Interface\n    config        *rest.Config\n}\n\ntype QuotaConfig struct {\n    Namespace      string\n    DefaultCPU     string\n    DefaultMemory  string\n    MaxCPU         string\n    MaxMemory      string\n    MaxSandboxes   int64\n}\n\ntype ClusterConfig struct {\n    AllowedRuntimes []string\n    DefaultNamespace string\n    EnableMonitoring bool\n}\n```\n\n### agentcube-shell (Interactive Shell)\n\n```go\ntype Shell struct {\n    clientset     versioned.Interface\n    kubeClient    kubernetes.Interface\n    restClient    *rest.RESTClient\n    sandboxName   string\n    namespace     string\n    shellType     string  // bash, sh, zsh\n}\n\ntype SessionConfig struct {\n    Timeout        time.Duration\n    IdleTimeout    time.Duration\n    HistoryFile    string\n    MaxHistory     int\n}\n```\n\n### agentcube-proxy (API Proxy)\n\n```go\ntype Proxy struct {\n    clientset     versioned.Interface\n    localPort     int\n    targetPort    int\n    namespace     string\n    resourceType  string  // agentruntime, codeinterpreter\n    resourceName  string\n}\n\ntype ProxyConfig struct {\n    ListenAddress  string\n    ListenPort     int\n    TLS            bool\n    TLSCert        string\n    TLSKey         string\n    AuthToken      string\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### agentcube Commands\n\n```bash\n# Sandbox management\nagentcube sandbox create <name> [--runtime=<type>] [--namespace=<ns>] [--cpu=<req>] [--memory=<req>]\nagentcube sandbox get <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [-o=json|yaml]\nagentcube sandbox list [--namespace=<ns>] [-l=<labels>]\nagentcube sandbox delete <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [--force]\nagentcube sandbox watch <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [--timeout=<duration>]\n\n# Runtime management\nagentcube runtime create <name> --spec=<file> [--namespace=<ns>]\nagentcube runtime get <name> [--namespace=<ns>] [-o=json|yaml]\nagentcube runtime list [--namespace=<ns>]\nagentcube runtime update <name> --spec=<file>\nagentcube runtime delete <name> [--namespace=<ns>]\n\n# Utility\nagentcube version\nagentcube completion <bash|zsh|fish>\nagentcube config view\nagentcube config set <key>=<value>\n```\n\n### agentcube-admin Commands\n\n```bash\n# Quota management\nagentcube-admin quota set <namespace> --cpu=<default> --memory=<default> --max-cpu=<max> --max-memory=<max>\nagentcube-admin quota get <namespace>\nagentcube-admin quota list\n\n# Cluster configuration\nagentcube-admin config get\nagentcube-admin config update --file=<config>\n\n# Health & diagnostics\nagentcube-admin health check\nagentcube-admin health report [-o=json|yaml]\n\n# Cleanup\nagentcube-admin cleanup idle [--older-than=<duration>]\nagentcube-admin cleanup failed [--namespace=<ns>]\n```\n\n### agentcube-shell Commands\n\n```bash\n# Interactive access\nagentcube-shell connect <sandbox-name> [--namespace=<ns>] [--shell=<type>]\nagentcube-shell exec <sandbox-name> <command> [--namespace=<ns>]\nagentcube-shell cp <sandbox-name>:<src> <dst> [--namespace=<ns>]\nagentcube-shell port-forward <sandbox-name> <local-port>:<remote-port>\n\n# Session management\nagentcube-shell sessions list\nagentcube-shell sessions kill <session-id>\n```\n\n### agentcube-proxy Commands\n\n```bash\n# API proxy\nagentcube-proxy start --resource=<type>/<name> --port=<local-port> [--namespace=<ns>]\nagentcube-proxy start --api-server --port=<local-port>\n\n# Status\nagentcube-proxy status\nagentcube-proxy stop\n```\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Shared Libraries\n\n```go\n// pkg/cliutil/config.go\ntype ClientConfig struct {\n    Kubeconfig   string\n    Context      string\n    Namespace    string\n    APIServer    string\n    Token        string\n    Timeout      time.Duration\n}\n\nfunc LoadConfig() (*ClientConfig, error)\nfunc (c *ClientConfig) GetClientset() (versioned.Interface, error)\nfunc (c *ClientConfig) GetInformerFactory() (informers.SharedInformerFactory, error)\n\n// pkg/cliutil/output.go\nfunc PrintObject(obj runtime.Object, format string) error\nfunc PrintTable(rows [][]string, headers []string) error\nfunc PrintStatus(status string, format string) error\n\n// pkg/cliutil/validation.go\nfunc ValidateSandboxName(name string) error\nfunc ValidateRuntimeType(rt string, allowed []string) error\nfunc ValidateResourceQuantity(q string) error\n```\n\n### agentcube - Main CLI\n\n```go\n// cmd/agentcube/main.go\nfunc main() {\n    rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:   \"agentcube\",\n        Short: \"AgentCube CLI for managing agent runtimes and sandboxes\",\n    }\n    \n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"namespace\", \"default\", \"namespace\")\n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().StringP(\"output\", \"o\", \"table\", \"output format\")\n    \n    rootCmd.AddCommand(sandboxCmd, runtimeCmd, configCmd, versionCmd)\n    \n    if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n}\n\n// cmd/agentcube/sandbox.go\nfunc newSandboxCreateCmd() *cobra.Command {\n    opts := &SandboxOptions{}\n    cmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:   \"create <name>\",\n        Args:  cobra.ExactArgs(1),\n        RunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n            opts.Name = args[0]\n            return runSandboxCreate(opts)\n        },\n    }\n    cmd.Flags().StringVar(&opts.RuntimeType, \"runtime\", \"jupyter\", \"runtime type\")\n    cmd.Flags().StringVar(&opts.CPURequest, \"cpu\", \"100m\", \"CPU request\")\n    cmd.Flags().StringVar(&opts.MemoryRequest, \"memory\", \"256Mi\", \"memory request\")\n    return cmd\n}\n\nfunc runSandboxCreate(opts *SandboxOptions) error {\n    cfg, err := cliutil.LoadConfig()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    clientset, err := cfg.GetClientset()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    // Construct CodeInterpreter object\n    ci := &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      opts.Name,\n            Namespace: opts.Namespace,\n            Labels:    opts.Labels,\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n            RuntimeType: opts.RuntimeType,\n            Resources: v1.ResourceRequirements{\n                Requests: v1.ResourceList{\n                    v1.ResourceCPU:    resource.MustParse(opts.CPURequest),\n                    v1.ResourceMemory: resource.MustParse(opts.MemoryRequest),\n                },\n            },\n        },\n    }\n    \n    result, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(opts.Namespace).Create(\n        cmd.Context(), ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    return cliutil.PrintObject(result, cfg.OutputFormat)\n}\n```\n\n### agentcube-admin - Admin CLI\n\n```go\n// cmd/agentcube-admin/main.go\nfunc main() {\n    rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:   \"agentcube-admin\",\n        Short: \"AgentCube Admin CLI for cluster administration\",\n    }\n    \n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"context\", \"\", \"kubeconfig context\")\n    \n    rootCmd.AddCommand(quotaCmd, configCmd, healthCmd, cleanupCmd)\n    \n    if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n}\n\n// cmd/agentcube-admin/quota.go\nfunc runQuotaSet(namespace string, cfg *QuotaConfig) error {\n    clientset, kubeClient, err := getAdminClients()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    // Check if namespace exists\n    _, err = kubeClient.CoreV1().Namespaces().Get(context.Background(), namespace, metav1.GetOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"namespace %q not found: %w\", namespace, err)\n    }\n    \n    // Create/update resource quota\n    quota := &v1.ResourceQuota{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"agentcube-quota\",\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n        Spec: v1.ResourceQuotaSpec{\n            Hard: v1.ResourceList{\n                v1.ResourceRequestsCPU:    resource.MustParse(cfg.DefaultCPU),\n                v1.ResourceRequestsMemory: resource.MustParse(cfg.DefaultMemory),\n                v1.ResourceLimitsCPU:      resource.MustParse(cfg.MaxCPU),\n                v1.ResourceLimitsMemory:   resource.MustParse(cfg.MaxMemory),\n            },\n        },\n    }\n    \n    _, err = kubeClient.CoreV1().ResourceQuotas(namespace).Create(\n        context.Background(), quota, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n        _, err = kubeClient.CoreV1().ResourceQuotas(namespace).Update(\n            context.Background(), quota, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n    }\n    \n    return err\n}\n```\n\n### agentcube-shell - Interactive Shell\n\n```go\n// cmd/agentcube-shell/main.go\nfunc main() {\n    rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:   \"agentcube-shell\",\n        Short: \"AgentCube Interactive Shell for sandbox access\",\n    }\n    \n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"namespace\", \"default\", \"namespace\")\n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().Duration(\"timeout\", 30*time.Minute, \"session timeout\")\n    \n    rootCmd.AddCommand(connectCmd, execCmd, cpCmd, portForwardCmd, sessionsCmd)\n    \n    if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n}\n\n// cmd/agentcube-shell/connect.go\nfunc runConnect(sandboxName string, cfg *SessionConfig) error {\n    clientset, kubeClient, restConfig := getShellClients()\n    \n    // Get sandbox\n    ci, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(cfg.Namespace).Get(\n        context.Background(), sandboxName, metav1.GetOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    if ci.Status.Phase != runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterRunning {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox is not running (phase: %s)\", ci.Status.Phase)\n    }\n    \n    // Get pod name from status\n    podName := ci.Status.PodName\n    if podName == \"\" {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox pod name not available\")\n    }\n    \n    // Establish SPDY connection for exec\n    req := kubeClient.CoreV1().RESTClient().Post().\n        Resource(\"pods\").\n        Name(podName).\n        Namespace(cfg.Namespace).\n        SubResource(\"exec\").\n        Param(\"container\", \"sandbox\").\n        Param(\"stdin\", \"true\").\n        Param(\"stdout\", \"true\").\n        Param(\"stderr\", \"true\").\n        Param(\"tty\", \"true\").\n        Param(\"command\", cfg.ShellType)\n    \n    executor, err := remotecommand.NewSPDYExecutor(restConfig, \"POST\", req.URL())\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    // Attach terminal\n    return executor.StreamWithContext(context.Background(), remotecommand.StreamOptions{\n        Stdin:  os.Stdin,\n        Stdout: os.Stdout,\n        Stderr: os.Stderr,\n        Tty:    true,\n    })\n}\n```\n\n### agentcube-proxy - API Proxy\n\n```go\n// cmd/agentcube-proxy/main.go\nfunc main() {\n    rootCmd := &cobra.Command{\n        Use:   \"agentcube-proxy\",\n        Short: \"AgentCube API Proxy for local port forwarding\",\n    }\n    \n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"path to kubeconfig\")\n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().String(\"listen\", \"127.0.0.1\", \"listen address\")\n    rootCmd.PersistentFlags().Int(\"port\", 8080, \"listen port\")\n    \n    rootCmd.AddCommand(startCmd, statusCmd, stopCmd)\n    \n    if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n}\n\n// cmd/agentcube-proxy/start.go\nfunc runProxy(opts *ProxyConfig) error {\n    clientset, restConfig := getProxyClients()\n    \n    // Build transport with auth\n    transport, err := rest.TransportFor(restConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    // Create reverse proxy\n    targetURL := restConfig.Host\n    proxy := httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(targetURL)\n    proxy.Transport = transport\n    \n    // Add authentication header\n    baseHandler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        if opts.AuthToken != \"\" {\n            if token := r.Header.Get(\"Authorization\"); token != \"Bearer \"+opts.AuthToken {\n                http.Error(w, \"unauthorized\", http.StatusUnauthorized)\n                return\n            }\n        }\n        proxy.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n    })\n    \n    server := &http.Server{\n        Addr:    fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", opts.ListenAddress, opts.ListenPort),\n        Handler: baseHandler,\n    }\n    \n    if opts.TLS {\n        return server.ListenAndServeTLS(opts.TLSCert, opts.TLSKey)\n    }\n    \n    return server.ListenAndServe()\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories\n\n```go\n// pkg/cliutil/errors.go\ntype CLIError struct {\n    Code    string\n    Message string\n    Err     error\n}\n\nfunc (e *CLIError) Error() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"[%s] %s: %v\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Err)\n}\n\n// Error codes\nconst (\n    ErrConfigNotFound   = \"CONFIG_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrAuthFailed       = \"AUTH_FAILED\"\n    ErrResourceNotFound = \"RESOURCE_NOT_FOUND\"\n    ErrResourceExists   = \"RESOURCE_EXISTS\"\n    ErrInvalidInput     = \"INVALID_INPUT\"\n    ErrTimeout          = \"TIMEOUT\"\n    ErrInternal         = \"INTERNAL\"\n)\n\nfunc NewCLIError(code, msg string, err error) *CLIError {\n    return &CLIError{Code: code, Message: msg, Err: err}\n}\n\nfunc WrapError(err error, msg string) *CLIError {\n    return &CLIError{Code: ErrInternal, Message: msg, Err: err}\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n1. **Configuration errors**: Clear message + path to fix\n2. **API errors**: Show resource name, namespace, and API response\n3. **Validation errors**: List all validation failures\n4. **Timeout errors**: Suggest increasing timeout or checking resource status\n5. **Internal errors**: Include correlation ID for debugging\n\n```go\nfunc handleError(err error) {\n    var cliErr *CLIError\n    if errors.As(err, &cliErr) {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error %s: %s\\n\", cliErr.Code, cliErr.Message)\n        if cliErr.Err != nil {\n            fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Caused by: %v\\n\", cliErr.Err)\n        }\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n    \n    // Handle Kubernetes API errors\n    if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: resource not found\\n\")\n    } else if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: resource already exists\\n\")\n    } else if apierrors.IsForbidden(err) {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: permission denied\\n\")\n    } else {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: %v\\n\", err)\n    }\n    os.Exit(1)\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```go\n// cmd/agentcube/sandbox_test.go\nfunc TestRunSandboxCreate(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        opts    *SandboxOptions\n        wantErr bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name: \"valid options\",\n            opts: &SandboxOptions{\n                Name:        \"test-sandbox\",\n                Namespace:   \"default\",\n                RuntimeType: \"jupyter\",\n            },\n            wantErr: false,\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"invalid runtime type\",\n            opts: &SandboxOptions{\n                Name:        \"test-sandbox\",\n                RuntimeType: \"invalid\",\n            },\n            wantErr: true,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            // Use fake clientset\n            clientset := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n            err := runSandboxCreateWithClient(tt.opts, clientset)\n            if (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n                t.Errorf(\"runSandboxCreate() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n            }\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```go\n// test/integration/cli_test.go\nfunc TestSandboxCreateGetDelete(t *testing.T) {\n    // Skip if no cluster available\n    if testing.Short() {\n        t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n    }\n    \n    // Create test namespace\n    ns := createTestNamespace(t)\n    defer deleteTestNamespace(t, ns)\n    \n    // Create sandbox via CLI\n    cmd := exec.Command(\"agentcube\", \"sandbox\", \"create\", \"test-sandbox\",\n        \"--namespace\", ns, \"--runtime\", \"jupyter\")\n    output, err := cmd.CombinedOutput()\n    if err != nil {\n        t.Fatalf(\"sandbox create failed: %v\\n%s\", err, output)\n    }\n    \n    // Get sandbox\n    cmd = exec.Command(\"agentcube\", \"sandbox\", \"get\", \"test-sandbox\",\n        \"--namespace\", ns, \"-o\", \"json\")\n    output, err = cmd.CombinedOutput()\n    if err != nil {\n        t.Fatalf(\"sandbox get failed: %v\\n%s\", err, output)\n    }\n    \n    // Delete sandbox\n    cmd = exec.Command(\"agentcube\", \"sandbox\", \"delete\", \"test-sandbox\",\n        \"--namespace\", ns)\n    output, err = cmd.CombinedOutput()\n    if err != nil {\n        t.Fatalf(\"sandbox delete failed: %v\\n%s\", err, output)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### E2E Tests\n\n```go\n// test/e2e/cli_e2e_test.go\nfunc TestFullWorkflow(t *testing.T) {\n    // Full workflow: create -> verify -> exec -> delete\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    \n    // Create\n    err := runAgentcube(ctx, \"sandbox\", \"create\", \"e2e-test\", \"--runtime\", \"python\")\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Wait for running\n    require.NoError(t, waitForSandboxRunning(ctx, \"e2e-test\"))\n    \n    // Execute command\n    output, err := runAgentcubeShell(ctx, \"exec\", \"e2e-test\", \"python\", \"-c\", \"print('hello')\")\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Contains(t, output, \"hello\")\n    \n    // Cleanup\n    runAgentcube(ctx, \"sandbox\", \"delete\", \"e2e-test\", \"--force\")\n}\n```\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `cmd/agentcube/main.go` | Main CLI entry point |\n| `cmd/agentcube/sandbox.go` | Sandbox subcommands |\n| `cmd/agentcube/runtime.go` | Runtime subcommands |\n| `cmd/agentcube/config.go` | Configuration commands |\n| `cmd/agentcube-admin/main.go` | Admin CLI entry point |\n| `cmd/agentcube-admin/quota.go` | Quota management |\n| `cmd/agentcube-admin/health.go` | Health checks |\n| `cmd/agentcube-admin/cleanup.go` | Cleanup operations |\n| `cmd/agentcube-shell/main.go` | Shell CLI entry point |\n| `cmd/agentcube-shell/connect.go` | Interactive connect |\n| `cmd/agentcube-shell/exec.go` | Remote exec |\n| `cmd/agentcube-proxy/main.go` | Proxy CLI entry point |\n| `cmd/agentcube-proxy/start.go` | Proxy server |\n| `pkg/cliutil/config.go` | Shared config loading |\n| `pkg/cliutil/output.go` | Output formatting |\n| `pkg/cliutil/errors.go` | Error types |\n| `pkg/cliutil/validation.go` | Input validation |\n| `test/integration/cli_test.go` | Integration tests |\n| `test/e2e/cli_e2e_test.go` | E2E tests |\n\n## Build & Installation\n\n### Makefile Targets\n\n```makefile\n# Build all binaries\nbuild-cli:\n    go build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n    go build -o bin/agentcube-admin ./cmd/agentcube-admin\n    go build -o bin/agentcube-shell ./cmd/agentcube-shell\n    go build -o bin/agentcube-proxy ./cmd/agentcube-proxy\n\n# Install to GOPATH\ninstall-cli:\n    go install ./cmd/agentcube\n    go install ./cmd/agentcube-admin\n    go install ./cmd/agentcube-shell\n    go install ./cmd/agentcube-proxy\n\n# Cross-compile\nbuild-all-platforms:\n    GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/linux/amd64/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n    GOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/darwin/amd64/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n    GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/windows/amd64/agentcube.exe ./cmd/agentcube\n```\n\n### Release Artifacts\n\n- `agentcube-linux-amd64`, `agentcube-darwin-amd64`, `agentcube-windows-amd64.exe`\n- `agentcube-admin-linux-amd64`, etc.\n- `agentcube-shell-linux-amd64`, etc.\n- `agentcube-proxy-linux-amd64`, etc.\n- Shell completion scripts: `agentcube-completion.bash`, `agentcube-completion.zsh`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/agentd/main.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/cmd/design.md","time":{"start":1775864160902,"end":1775864160913}}}}
